  "detailedRequirements": "<div class=\"previewMask\">\n<h1><span class=\"small_info_spec\" id=\"rswDetailedRequirements\"><span class=\"small_info_spec\" id=\"rswDetailedRequirements\"><span class=\"small_info_spec\" id=\"rswDetailedRequirements\"><span class=\"small_info_spec\" id=\"rswDetailedRequirements\"><span class=\"small_info_spec\" id=\"rswDetailedRequirements\"><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\">Project Overview</span></span></span></span></span></span></h1>\n\n<p><span class=\"small_info_spec\" id=\"rswDetailedRequirements\"><span class=\"small_info_spec\" id=\"rswDetailedRequirements\"><span class=\"small_info_spec\" id=\"rswDetailedRequirements\"><span class=\"small_info_spec\" id=\"rswDetailedRequirements\"><span class=\"small_info_spec\" id=\"rswDetailedRequirements\">Currently, TopCoder Competition Engine used a customized way for communication between the client side (Arena applet) and the backend listeners. We are implementing a Web-based Arena based Web Socket protocol.</span></span></span></span></span>&nbsp; So the frontend and backend are properly decoupled.</p>\n\n<p><span class=\"small_info_spec\" id=\"rswDetailedRequirements\"><span class=\"small_info_spec\" id=\"rswDetailedRequirements\"><span class=\"small_info_spec\" id=\"rswDetailedRequirements\"><span class=\"small_info_spec\" id=\"rswDetailedRequirements\"><span class=\"small_info_spec\" id=\"rswDetailedRequirements\">Previously,&nbsp; we have implemented the first part of the web arena </span></span></span></span>using AngularJS Framework (<a href=\"http://angularjs.org/\">http://angularjs.org</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://docs.angularjs.org/guide\">http://docs.angularjs.org/guide</a>) and Bootstrap 3 (<a href=\"http://getbootstrap.com/getting-started\">http://getbootstrap.com/getting-started</a>).</span></p>\n\n<h1><span class=\"small_info_spec\" id=\"rswDetailedRequirements\"><span class=\"small_info_spec\" id=\"rswDetailedRequirements\"><span class=\"small_info_spec\" id=\"rswDetailedRequirements\"><span class=\"small_info_spec\" id=\"rswDetailedRequirements\"><span class=\"small_info_spec\" id=\"rswDetailedRequirements\"><span style=\"color:#FF0000;\">Competition Task Overview</span></span></span></span></span></span></h1>\n\n<p><span class=\"small_info_spec\" id=\"rswDetailedRequirements\"><span class=\"small_info_spec\" id=\"rswDetailedRequirements\"><span class=\"small_info_spec\" id=\"rswDetailedRequirements\"><span class=\"small_info_spec\" id=\"rswDetailedRequirements\"><span class=\"small_info_spec\" id=\"rswDetailedRequirements\"><span style=\"font-size:12px;\">This contest is would like to explore the way to do heroku deployment for <a href=\"https://github.com/cloudspokes/arena-web\">web arena</a>.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p><span class=\"small_info_spec\"><span class=\"small_info_spec\"><span class=\"small_info_spec\"><span class=\"small_info_spec\"><span class=\"small_info_spec\"><span style=\"font-size:12px;\">We are expecting <u>a shell script</u> similar as </span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"css-truncate css-truncate-target\"><a class=\"js-directory-link\" href=\"https://github.com/cloudspokes/tc-api/blob/master/deploy/heroku.sh\" id=\"f91dfc91a95d8bd64854bf0f389b0793-d6ae43e4390f4df7b7f46f6a9ee14a78ca4ca75c\" title=\"heroku.sh\">heroku.sh</a>&nbsp; </span>for TC API and general description for how to use it.</p>\n\n<p>You just need to support <u>config</u>, <u>push </u>and <u>launch</u>, which can deploy the projects to the Heroku cloud.</p>\n\n<p>You can check <a href=\"https://github.com/cloudspokes/tc-api/wiki/Heroku-Deployment-Guide\">https://github.com/cloudspokes/tc-api/wiki/Heroku-Deployment-Guide</a> for general reference.</p>\n</div>\n",
